org.sosy_lab.solver.basicimpl.tactics

Enum Tactic

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Tactic>
      • org.sosy_lab.solver.basicimpl.tactics.Tactic
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Tactic>

    public enum Tactic
extends Enum<Tactic>
    Enum that holds all the values for tactics that are either supported with a default implementation in java-smt or with a solver-specific version e.g. via z3.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NNF

        public static final Tactic NNF
        Convert the formula to NNF. Equivalence, ITE and implications are resolved" by replacing them with appropriate formulas consisting of and/or/not.

        This tactic has a default implementation.

      • CNF_LIGHT

        public static final Tactic CNF_LIGHT
        Convert the formula to an approximated CNF. This tactic creates a CNF formula but still may have some 'ands' which are deeper stacked in the formula and thus would create too much conjuncts when creating a full CNF.

        This tactic has a default implementation.

      • CNF

        public static final Tactic CNF
        Convert the formula to CNF. This tactic creates a formula which is in some cases exponentially bigger. E.g. (x /\ y) \/ (z /\ w) will have 2^n clauses in CNF afterwards.

        This tactic has a default implementation.

      • TSEITIN_CNF

        public static final Tactic TSEITIN_CNF
        Convert the formula to CNF using Tseitin encoding. Note that the resulting formula is not equivalent but only equisatisfiable.

        This tactic has no default implementation.

      • QE_LIGHT

        public static final Tactic QE_LIGHT
        Perform light quantifier elimination.

        This tactic has no default implementation.

      • QE

        public static final Tactic QE
        Perform quantifier elimination.

        This tactic has no default implementation.

      • applyDefault

        public BooleanFormula applyDefault(FormulaManager pFmgr,
                                   BooleanFormula pF)
        Applies the default implementation for the tactic on the given Formula and returns the result. Note that this may lead to different results and may be not as efficient as using solver-specific tactic implementations by calling FormulaManager#applyTactic(BooleanFormula, Tactic).

        Thus calling this method is discouraged.

        Parameters:
        pFmgr - The formula manager that created the given formula.
        pF - The formula to rewrite.
